[The count continues to grow. There have now been 53 cases of polio attributable to infection with WPV1 in Pakistan with dates of onset since 1 Jan 2019. Adding the 12 confirmed cases in Afghanistan brings the global tally of WPV1 associated AFP (acute flaccid paralysis) to 65.

According to End Polio Pakistan, there have now been 22 cases reported from Bannu, whereas it is the 1st case reported from Charsadda (the district is just north of Peshawar), and the 1st case reported from Razmak (located in South Waziristan) (see http://www.endpolio.com.pk/polioin-pakistan/polio-cases-district-wise-2019).

A map of Pakistan showing districts can be found at: https://reliefweb.int/sites/reliefweb.int/files/resources/pak215_pakistan_districts_v5_a0_20181203.pdf
A map showing the location of Razmat district can be found at: https://goo.gl/maps/PYEpG4XC4K2eJSoE8.
